Caption:
✨daily inspiration✨

It’s a brand new week, friends! I’m not sure about y’all, but I’m just really not feeling like myself today. As much as I want to be super inspirational and give you something profound to live for this week, I don’t have it in me.

Instead, I can tell you exactly what I’ve been trying to remind myself of today.

Take it one day at a time.

Not everyday is going to be great.
You won’t feel like your best self everyday.
Each day won’t be filled with loads of productivity.

If you’re also struggling today, just know that whatever you’re feeling won’t last forever. You’re not doomed. You’ll likely feel more hopeful tomorrow or the next day. 

You don’t have to have everything figured out today.
You don’t need to be perfectly positive all the time.
You don’t have to let your bad day result in hopelessness.

Just take it one day at a time—we’re gonna be okay whether it seems like it or not✨🌷

I love you and Jesus does too 🫶🏻 

💖B 

Visit me online at: https://bayleeonthedaily.com/

Caption:
Montessori sensorial materials are designed to help children (3-6years old) develop and refine their five senses: sight, sound, touch, taste, and smell. These materials are integral to the Montessori method and serve several key purposes:

1. Refinement of the Senses.
2. Foundation for Learning.
3. Development of Fine Motor Skills.
4. Promotion of Independence.
5. Order and Sequence.
6. Preparation for Mathematical Concepts.

Examples of Montessori sensorial materials include: Pink Tower, Brown Stair (Broad Stair), Knobbed Cylinders, Color Tablets, Sound Cylinders, Smelling Bottles, Rough and Smooth Boards.

These materials not only enhance sensory perception but also support cognitive development, laying a solid foundation for further learning in various disciplines.

~To Educate The Total Child For God and Humanity.

Caption:
Temple #88 Columbia South Carolina April 4, 2024. 

The Columbia South Carolina temple is the 62nd operating temple of the Church. The temple was dedicated on October 17, 1999, by Gordan B. Hinckley. 

Four Temples, Four States, Two Days, One Crazy Adventure.

 Our temple trip was ambitious, to say the least. Four states, four temples, all crammed into a whirlwind two days. It felt audacious, borderline nonsensical, but we were determined to pull it off.

My work travels took me to Charlotte Airport, where we regrouped and set off for our first stop: Columbia, South Carolina.  We didn't have any remarkable experiences but enjoyed the session. The temple had serene grounds with their swaying palm trees provided a welcome respite.  Knowing the tight schedule ahead, we soaked up the tranquility for a bit before moving on.

The history of the Church in South Carolina goes back to the earliest days of the Church in the 1830s. An early church missionary, Lysander M. Davis arrived in South Carolina in 1839 and discovered that a convert, Emmanuel Masters Murphy, had been teaching the gospel message in the area. Together, these men helped the Church grow. The first branch (small congregation) was organized in 1917. Since that time, the Church has grown tremendously in South Carolina.

Caption: It's June, it will always be June to me. I will not honor a month dedicated to the mockery of God just as I will not bow to any king but him. What God established as a covenant between Noah and every living creature to never destroy the earth entirely by flood again and made the rainbow as a reminder of that covenant, Satan took and twisted. The very things God destroyed the earth over, Satan uses to mock him. The original 7 color rainbow of God has been turned into a 6-color PRIDE flag thus taking the completeness in that number and turning it into a lie. As the years have gone by, more colors and symbolism have been added to the original flag adopted in 1979, but one thing remains the same. PRIDE goes before destruction and God will not be mocked. We as Christians cannot partake in what will turn us from God. We are not to judge, but to lovingly show the way back to God's grace and to turn away from the sin and perverseness PRIDE month represents. Do your research, on where to Godly spend your time and money as the acceptance of the sin associated with PRIDE month is everywhere. Teach your children in the ways of the Lord so they will stand firm in the Word as God's mouthpiece and to bring the lost back to Christ. Pray for the believers to not fall prey to the sin in this sinful society we have created. #God #Jesus #Jesussaves #believer #bodyofbelievers #christian #christianmom

Caption:
Pablo dijo a los filipenses: “…nosotros somos…los que en espíritu servimos a Dios y nos gloriamos en Cristo Jesús, no teniendo confianza en la carne” (Fil. 3:3). Juan 4:23 dice: “Los verdaderos adoradores adorarán al Padre en espíritu y en verdad”. Somos llamados a ofrecer nuestro cuerpo como un sacrificio vivo a Dios en un acto santo de adoración (Ro. 12:1). Pedro dijo que somos “sacerdocio santo, para ofrecer sacrificios espirituales aceptables a Dios por medio de Jesucristo” (1 P. 2:5)

Cuando usted va a la iglesia, ¿piensa de verdad acerca de los himnos que canta o medita en las cosas que escucha, que están enseñando y predicando? Usted necesita cultivar un corazón que adora. Y su adoración no debiera estar limitada a cuando va al templo. El culto que se celebra en el templo debiera ser el catalítico que le mueve a adorar en todo tiempo. En The Ultimate Priority [La prioridad final] (Chicago: Moody, 1983) yo decía que adoramos mejor cuando somos completamente obedientes. Obediencia es la definición básica de adoración. Al igual que la obediencia, la adoración tiene que ser una forma de vida en vez de solo un ejercicio religioso de los domingos.

Hebreos 10:22 nos invita a que nos acerquemos a Dios. Santiago 4:8 es más específico: “Acercaos a Dios, y él se acercará a vosotros”. ¿Se ha acercado usted alguna vez a Dios con prisas? ¿Permite usted que su corazón y mente asciendan cuando escucha los himnos, la lectura de las Escrituras o la oración? ¿Medita usted con profunda devoción? Recuerde, tenemos que ser un pueblo que adora.

Extraído del libro, “El Plan del Señor Para La Iglesia” escrito por el Pastor John MacArthur

 #adoracion  #worship  #christian

Caption:
Are you fighting any battles in your mind? 🏳️

Lately, I have had a lot of anxiety. It feels like a constant battle in my mind until I take the time to pray and talk to my Heavenly Father, and then it silences. Then I have to remain on constant watch so that the war does not start up again. 

Whatever battle you are facing in your life, God can silence it. He can wave that white flag of peace and help you find solutions in your life. If it is a battle that's not quite over yet, He will fight right along with you if you invite Him to. You are fighting a battle Jesus has already won, ask him for help when you are struggling and he will help you win it too!

Peace Treaty by Daisy Duncan

Caption:
Kayak Girl by Ivy Emerson
(Hilton Head Island Series 1)

Kayak Girl was my first Christian romance that I’ve read and I loved it. It was a fun summer read and demonstrated God’s grace and forgiveness for us. There was also reminders of how we can be so stubborn at times wanting to hear God, but we aren’t hearing what He’s saying because it’s not what we want. How we need to give everything to God and not let our wants get in the way of His plan. 

In Kayak Girl, Elle is on a summer trip to explore new kayaking spots and run away from responsibilities. Gray is focusing on the summer camp his church puts on. Both have sworn off relationships, but have an instant attraction. When they keep getting put in situations where they have to work together their connection grows. But when there’s an accident Elle doesn’t know how to be honest and not be scared on confrontation. Looking to God and her new friends she tries to learn how to take responsibility. 

This book has themes of:
🌊 Christian
🌊 Instant connection
🌊 Summer vibes
🌊 Learning to trust
🌊 Finding yourself

Caption:
This Pride Month we are examining the original meanings of the colors on the first pride flag. We hope that this exercise in remembrance will help us to honor the LGBTQ+ ancestors and activists who came before us, love and celebrate ourselves and the wider queer community, and inspire us to join in a long line of queer artists, activists, poets, and protestors who have insisted upon a more just and inclusive world.

The theme colors for this first week of pride are red and orange. Red symbolizes passion and life, the powerful energy and determination of LGBTQ+ activists throughout history. Orange represents healing and recovery, honoring the many journeys of resilience, self-acceptance, and communal healing within the LGBTQ+ community. 

Read the full blog post at the link in our bio!

[Image Description: Orange and red gradient background, in the center in white text reads a quote from the blog post: "By engaging as our whole selves, we are passionately fueled toward the healing of our own bodies, communities, and relationships, and those of the world.” - Millie Piper]

Caption:
#오늘의QT 
선행과 순종으로 복음을 보여 주는 성도 [베드로전서 2:11~25]

📖 오늘의 말씀
20 죄가 있어 매를 맞고 참으면 무슨 칭찬이 있으리요 그러나 선을 행함으로 고난을 받고 참으면 이는 하나님 앞에 아름다우니라

✍ 본문 해설 
베드로는 부르심의 상태나 형편이 어떻든지 성도는 ‘하나님 앞에서’ 합당한 태도를 취하는 것이 중요하다고 강조합니다. 그것이 성도를 위해 고난당하시며 친히 ‘본’을 보이신 예수 그리스도의 자취를 따라가는 길입니다(21절). ‘영혼의 목자와 감독되신’(25절) 하나님께 나아와 새로운 존재가 된 그리스도인은 세상과는 다른 기준으로 세상을 살아가야 합니다. 

🙏 오늘의 기도
주님, 보잘것없는 제 삶을 십자가 은혜로 구속하셔서 존귀한 인생으로 바꾸시니 감사합니다. 세상의 안락함과 멀어지고, 억울한 고난이 겹쳐와도 주님의 길을 포기하지 않고 따르게 하소서. 하나님을 경외하고 선한 일에 힘쓰며 주님을 기쁘시게 하는 신실한 종으로 살게 하소서. 아멘.

✅ 적용 질문 
윗 사람이 부당하게 대할 때 나의 반응은 어떤가요? 
*적용 질문의 답을 댓글에 남겨 묵상의 은혜를 나누어 주세요. 
-

_

Caption:
I went on my first trip out of the country. It was my first time flying on a plane. I went to Israel with my church family, @corechurchla . The trip was hosted by my pastor, @stevewilburn__   , and @imaginetours . I got to walk where Jesus walked. I enjoyed meeting new church members.

1) I'm standing on Mount Arbel.
2) I'm in Old Jaffa. The whale behind me represents the whale that swallowed Jonah. (Jonah 1:17).
3) Kelly, Jessica, and I are riding in the Sea of Galilee Worship Boat owned by Daniel Carmel.
4) Ms. Marilyn and I.
5) I'm at a public latrine in Bet-She'An.
6) Me holding sea salt and floating in the Dead Sea. I felt like I was floating in olive oil. My skin was baby soft when I got out
7) Lunch time at Abu Antar Restaurant.
8) Group shot at Ein Gedi Nature Reserve.
9) Group shot at the Dome of the Rock on Mount Moriah.
10) Pastor Steve and I at the farewell dinner.

Caption: The Anatomical Theatre of the Archiginnasio is a hall once used for anatomy lectures and displays held at the medical school in Bologna, Italy that used to be located in the Palace of the Archiginnasio, the first unified seat of the University of Bologna. A first anatomical theatre was constructed in 1595, in a different location, but it was replaced by a bigger one built in 1637 in the current location, following the design of the architect Antonio Levanti. The theatre underwent several modifications and reached its final shape between 1733 and 1736. In this period, Silvestro Giannotti carved the wooden statues which decorate the theatre walls. They represent some famous physicians of ancient times (Hippocrates, Galenus, etc.). \n\n#italy #ravenna #bologna #goths #byzantium #byzantine #byzance #byzantineempire #rome #romans #mosaic #theodora #livelaughtravel #instatravel #travelislife #lovelife #lovetravel #travelphotography #culture #tradition  #university #history #art #heritage #music #musicinstrument #christ #christian

Caption:
Ubwami bw’Imana niki? 

Ubwami bugomba kugira:
- Imipaka
- Ubukungu
- Ingabo zirinda ubwami (Ingabo)
- Umuco
- Umwami
- Abanyagihugu
- Amategeko….

Mu bwami, ibintu byose ni iby’umwami harimo n’abantu. Muri republika ibintu ni ibyabaturage. Ubwami bw’Imana rero bwujuje ibyangombwa byose by’ubwami ariko butandukanye mubutegetsi bwabwo n’Umwami.

Ubwami bwa Yesu ntibugira imipaka, ahantu hose ibyaremwe bikoraho aho ni ubwami bwe kandi, turi abana (Yohana 1: 10-13) n’abenegihugu b’ubwo Bwami.

Ubwami bw’Imana ni ishingiro ry’ubutumwa bwiza bwa Yesu Kristo. Imana yahishuye ubwami bw’Imana muburyo 2:

- Ubwami bwo mw’ijuru (Matayo 5:20)
- Ubwami bw’Imana (Luka 17: 20-21

Itegekonshinga ry’Ubwami bw’Imana riboneka muri Matayo 5: 1-12.

Niyo mpamvu Yesu atugira inama yo kubanza gushaka ubwami bw’Imana (Matayo 6:33). Tugomba kumenya uburenganzira ninshingano zacu mubwami. Bitabaye ibyo tuhinduka imbata mubwami bw’Imana aho kuba abana.

What is the kingdom of God?

A kingdom must have:
- Territory
- Resources (Economy)
- Forces protecting the kingdom (Army)
- Culture
- King
- Citizens
- Laws….

In a kingdom, everything belongs to the king including the people. In a republic things belong to the people. So the kingdom of God meets all credentials of a kingdom but differs in its ruling and King.

Jesus’s kingdom has no boundaries, wherever creation touches is part of His kingdom and we are children (John 1:10-13) and citizens of this Kingdom.

The Kingdom of God is the core of the Good news of Jesus Christ. God revealed the Kingdom of God in 2 ways:

- The kingdom of heaven (Matthew 5:20)
- The kingdom of God (Luke 17:20-21

The constitution of the Kingdom of God is found in Matthew 5:1-12.

This is why Jesus advises us to seek first the Kingdom of God (Matthew 6:33). We need to know our rights and responsibilities in the Kingdom otherwise we will become slaves in the Kingdom of God instead of children.

Caption:
Parola del  giorno 
🌿🌿🌿 Lunedì 3 giugno 2024🌿🌿🌿
I Lettura 2Pt 1,2-7
Dio ci ha donato i beni grandissimi e preziosi a noi promessi, affinché per loro mezzo diventiate partecipi della natura divina.
Salmo (Sal 90)
Mio Dio, in te confido.
Vangelo Mc 12,1-12
Presero il figlio amato, lo uccisero e lo gettarono fuori della vigna.
🐝🍯🐝🍯🐝🍯🐝🍯🐝🍯
In quel tempo, Gesù si mise a parlare con parabole [ai capi dei sacerdoti, agli scribi e agli anziani]:
«Un uomo piantò una vigna, la circondò con una siepe, scavò una buca per il torchio e costruì una torre. La diede in affitto a dei contadini e se ne andò lontano.
Al momento opportuno mandò un servo dai contadini a ritirare da loro la sua parte del raccolto della vigna. Ma essi lo presero, lo bastonarono e lo mandarono via a mani vuote. Mandò loro di nuovo un altro servo: anche quello lo picchiarono sulla testa e lo insultarono. Ne mandò un altro, e questo lo uccisero; poi molti altri: alcuni li bastonarono, altri li uccisero.
Ne aveva ancora uno, un figlio amato; lo inviò loro per ultimo, dicendo: “Avranno rispetto per mio figlio!”. Ma quei contadini dissero tra loro: “Costui è l’erede. Su, uccidiamolo e l’eredità sarà nostra”. Lo presero, lo uccisero e lo gettarono fuori della vigna.
Che cosa farà dunque il padrone della vigna? Verrà e farà morire i contadini e darà la vigna ad altri. Non avete letto questa Scrittura: “La pietra che i costruttori hanno scartato è diventata la pietra d’angolo; questo è stato fatto dal Signore ed è una meraviglia ai nostri occhi”?».
E cercavano di catturarlo, ma ebbero paura della folla; avevano capito infatti che aveva detto quella parabola contro di loro. Lo lasciarono e se ne andarono.

Caption:
David spoke of Jesus’ resurrection, as mentioned in verse 25. The scripture Peter refers to is Psalm 16:8-11, which, although partly about David, mainly refers to Jesus.

First, Peter quotes the text in full (verses 25-28) to show its complete fulfillment in Jesus. 

1. Jesus always focused on his Father’s glory in everything he did. He knew his sufferings would honor God and result in his own joy. This knowledge helped him endure his trials (John 13:31-32; 17:4-5).

2. Jesus was confident of his Father’s presence and power supporting him: “He is at my right hand, guiding and upholding me so I won’t be shaken from my mission, despite the hardships.” This confidence came from God’s promise to strengthen him (Psalm 89:21).

3. Despite the sorrows he faced, Jesus was cheerful in his work: “Knowing that I won’t be shaken and that God’s plan will succeed, my heart is glad, and my tongue is rejoices. The thought of my sorrow is nothing to me.” Jesus found constant pleasure in knowing the end of his work would be glorious. He rejoiced in spirit (Luke 10:21). ✞

Caption: I’ve spent most of my life trying to get “somewhere”. Make “something” of myself. Get to the “next big thing”. I’m tirelessly working to be better, do better. Caption:
💧🐑💧❤️💧🐑❤️
Still Waters Devotional 03/06/24
(The Em😍ji Dev😎ti🥰nal)
...He leads me beside the still waters Ps 23: 2

Inspiration Monday: The Shepherd's👳🏻‍♂️Heart.❤️(1️⃣)

The LORD is my shepherd; I have everything I need. 
Psalm 23:1 (GNT)

In our key☝️ text for today,😃 The Lord is referred to as Our Shepherd.👳🏻‍♂️In the days, when the Bible📖 was written, shepherding🐑🐑 was a very important occupation.👌

A Shepherd👳🏻‍♂️ takes care of sheep🐑 in their numbers🐑🐑🐑 and they have a special kind🤗 of relationship ❤️with their sheep and it was a relationship🤗 that goes beyond just rearing sheep;🤔 it was full of affection🤗 and love❤️ for the sheep. A Shepherd could risk everything, even his life to save just one1️⃣ sheep, that was how selfless they were.🤗🐑

So, The Lord is our Shepherd!👳🏻‍♂️🙌 The Bible📖 makes us to understand the heart ❤️of the Shepherd for His flock is a large one.💪

So let's take a look👀 at the Shepherd's heart.👉❤️What is on our Heavenly☝️ Shepherd's👳🏻‍♂️ heart ❤️for you today?🤔

1️⃣ To The World ,🌍You Are Just A Sheep, 🐑But To Jesus☝️ You Are The World!🤗

You👉 mean so much🤗 to Jesus, He cares 🤗about you! He loves❤️❤️ you! You are on His mind!🤔 He holds🤗 you close to His heart❤️ and carries you in His arms...🤗🤩When you went missing🤔 in a flock of 1️⃣0️⃣0️⃣, He left the 9️⃣9️⃣ to find you 😌and brought you back home safely.👍He gave 🙌His life for you!👉

Caption:
#HappyPride 2024!

I write to you as a parent of young adults who identify as part of the LGBTQIA+ community and as a Christian, Presbyterian, religious leader who grew up in and has LED affirming communities. This year, I again join others in publicly and boldly affirming a part of the beloved community that too many of my Christian siblings do not.

While there are many in the church who are LGBTQIA+ affirming, AND I will rejoice in the day that you can assume safety and affirmation in Christian spaces, I know that many churches, campus ministries, and religious leaders have inflicted emotional, spiritual, and physical trauma upon your personhood — all in the name of God.

I do not presume to speak for or apologize on behalf of these Christian communities, individuals, or leaders, but I do name and lament the pain that has been heaped upon you by those with whom I share a common sacred text and a professed belief in the one called Jesus.

Too many Christians have bought into and preached a gospel of “Hate the sin, love the sinner.”  This theology disguises hate as love and perpetuates and emboldens a culture of homophobia, biphobia, transphobia, and queerphobia that has led to spiritual trauma, emotional abuse, physical violence, and death.

I and others lament this reality but make no mistake, we also reject this version of the Christian faith and want you to know that many of us affirm the fullness of your personhood, full stop.

Our affirmation is public and it is unequivocal.

I fully acknowledge that your humanity needs no affirmation by some random pastor and leader of a tradition that has historically weaponized a person's sexuality and gender in order to uphold power, influence, and wealth. 

That said, if there is any part of your soul that has yearned to hear an acknowledgment of pain caused, if you need to hear even a whisper of healing and hope, or if you have wondered if there are allies and accomplices out there, I hope you hear that from me and other people of faith, and not only during Pride — you are loved.

This Christian, Filipino/Chinese-Am dad, pastor, husband, and human loves you!

#Pride2024 #PrideMonth #LGBTQIA #Christian #PCUSA #aanhpi

Caption: This picture brought up memories of how my life used to be before the Lord came in & saved me...In the past I had used the rejection...hurt...abuse & words that others had put me through become the bars I used for my own cage...each situation caused me to withdraw even more into myself where I felt I could be safe & cope with how I was being treated...it was a life spent ceaselessly trying to please people who were incapable of being  pleased...my life became a regretful existence....I wasn’t doing much in life but just existing...waiting for the next hurt feeling like it was inevitable...but I eventually realized existing without truly living was not what I wanted for myself...I wanted a life that would inspire others...a life that could help change people to see their own worth & beauty...a life to bring smiles to the hurting...I had to give myself permission to grow...I learned not everyone who started with me will finish with me but its ok...I am willing to go alone sometimes because I am finally complete in me & know for the first time in my life exactly who I am & who I want to be <3. \n\n #happy #mindset #motivation #art #artist #travel #thoughts #soul #spiritual #christian #lawofattraction #meditation #funny #funnyvideos #quotes #photography #naturevibes #depression #inspiration #fashion #jesus #happines #smile #drama #highendart #graphicdesign  #coffee #jesus #bird

Caption:
I often tell my children, "Choose kindness." I'm realizing more and more how often I need to do that as well.
.
When you're frustrated with the person who just cut you off in traffic, choose kindness.
.
When you feel like someone is judging you at church, choose kindness.
.
When someone is rude to you at work, choose kindness.
.
When your order is messed up, choose kindness.
.
It's the strongest use of our agency that there is.
.
.

Caption: This picture brought up memories of how my life used to be before the Lord came in & saved me...In the past I had used the rejection...hurt...abuse & words that others had put me through become the bars I used for my own cage...each situation caused me to withdraw even more into myself where I felt I could be safe & cope with how I was being treated...it was a life spent ceaselessly trying to please people who were incapable of being  pleased...my life became a regretful existence....I wasn’t doing much in life but just existing...waiting for the next hurt feeling like it was inevitable...but I eventually realized existing without truly living was not what I wanted for myself...I wanted a life that would inspire others...a life that could help change people to see their own worth & beauty...a life to bring smiles to the hurting...I had to give myself permission to grow...I learned not everyone who started with me will finish with me but its ok...I am willing to go alone sometimes because I am finally complete in me & know for the first time in my life exactly who I am & who I want to be <3. \n\n #happy #mindset #motivation #art #artist #travel #thoughts #soul #spiritual #christian #lawofattraction #meditation #funny #funnyvideos #quotes #photography #naturevibes #depression #inspiration #fashion #jesus #happines #smile #drama #highendart #graphicdesign  #coffee #jesus #bird

Caption:
“Deacons are the servants of charity.” - #PopeFrancis

On Thursday, May 30th, Osman Enrique de la Hoz Escorcia CSB and Eduard Alexis Guerrero Carillo CSB were ordained as deacons in the San Basilio Parish of the Archdiocese of Medellín. The ordination was presided over by the Archbishop of Medellín, Monsignor Ricardo Tobón.

The ordination ceremony was attended by Fr. Pedro Mora CSB, as the delegate of the Superior General, and Fr. Juan Carlos Rojas Ramos CSB, Superior of San Basilio in Colombia. Also present were the Basilian priests: Fr. Carlos Rodríguez, Fr. Javier Higuera, and Fr. Alberto Rodríguez.

The newly ordained #deacons were accompanied by their families, coming from the Arboleda and Barranquilla regions of Colombia, as well as guest priests from the archdioceses of Bogotá and Medellín, missionaries from Parma, and friends of the Congregation.

As described in the Acts of the Apostles, seven deacons were selected to assist the Apostles in their work of serving widows and the poor. St. Stephen, a martyr, was the first deacon to be selected to serve the charitable causes of the early #Church.

The diaconate is a pivotal step in the process of ordination into the priesthood. Deriving from the Greek word “diaconia” – meaning “service” – only priests and deacons can read the Gospel, baptize, and witness marriages. Deacons cannot hear confessions, preside over #Mass, or anoint the sick.

We congratulate Osman and Eduard on this important milestone in their Basilian journey and wish them a blessed and fruitful ministry.

Congratulations! / ¡Felicidades! / Félicitations!

Caption:
No words can describe how much i love you Jesus..no words!! I’m relieved that you can see and feel my heart,
my good soul and how grateful i am for everything that you’ve done for me. SO SO SO grateful.

I have sinned many times for so long,i almost destroyed my self hitting bottom..i knew that i was going into a very dark path,so for the first time in my life,i called your name crying and drunk asking for your help,you didn’t made me wait..
i feel asleep,and the next morning,i felt lighter,
and didn’t wanna drink anymore after years of bad habits,i was lazy,but from that morning no day passed by that
 I didn’t work out.
I removed all fake and envy people around me and started fresh all by myself! 
My head became clearer and I saw all the red flags around me,from people,to habits and places.
Everyday I become stronger and faster.

You never left my side,even when I was sinning and cursing all day. You always protected me from dangerous situations,VERY  dangerous.
I was blind,and influenced by the evil,thanks to you I had always this gut feeling that I was doing the wrong things,but I couldn’t find the courage to change….until I was FED UP!
You always blessed me,from birth and in every single aspect of my life. You did AMAZING things for me,so grateful!
I’ll be nothing without you,I’m trying my best to live the life how you wish and command..is not easy but is worth the pain! 
I’m honored to call you my savior,my king,my everything.
Cannot wait to hug you.

Caption:
Let’s talk about it!

The Proverbs 31 woman is often upheld as the ideal for Biblical womanhood, and as she should be - the Bible indicates her as a wonderful example for us to strive after. The trouble is, she is often misrepresented in Evangelical culture as a subservient, silent stay-at-home-wife, molding her to fit modern Evangelical culture’s vision of an ideal woman rather than the reverse. If that ideal for Biblical womanhood were true, the Proverbs 31 woman wouldn’t be the example Scripture calls us to; if anything she’d be condemned.

The Proverbs 31 woman:
- conducts business (verse 16)
- makes and sells merchandise (verses 18 & 24)
- speaks with wisdom and kind teaching (verse 26)

Moreover, her husband, rather than being threatened by his wife’s capabilities and contributions, praises her for the work she has done and for her character (verses 28-31).

The Proverbs 31 wife is not a subservient, silent housewife, but a well-rounded woman who loves her husband and children while also serving them and her community with her gifts, including her gifts for conducting business and selling merchandise. These are the sorts of things Evangelical culture argues belong only to men, despite the fact that the Proverbs 31 woman herself contributes to and serves her loved ones by using her gifts in these areas. Moreover, had God intended that women never use their voices in their households and believed that we could never learn anything from women, the Proverbs 31 woman would not have been praised for her wisdom and teaching of kindness. The Proverbs 31 woman is one of many reasons it is clear that Scripture does not argue for the subjugated housewife - it is sinful humanity that does.

Caption:
Someone once made a comment saying they wish they had a desire to read the Bible or they wish it was not boring or hard to understand. [I definitely used to feel this way!] 
What I can tell you is to get that “hunger” or “drive” you have to discipline yourself to sit down to read it, no matter if you feel like it or not! The more time you spend reading the Word the more you’ll understand and the more you understand the. more you’ll want to read. If you read something you don’t understand make sure you pray about it or ask a mentor for guidance. Sometimes God will show you the meaning far after you read it… for example I’ve read scripture and didn’t understand it and a week or 2 later something happened in my life and I thought about that scripture I read weeks ago and it made sense!! 
.
The Bible is there to teach us what is true and make us realize what’s wrong in our lives. Correct us when we are wrong and teaches us to do right. So why wouldn’t you want to read it and raise your kids through His Word?
.
.
.
#BibleTime #quiettime #prayer #GodsTruth #Christian #scripture #godfirst

Caption:
Propósito! 🤍
A vida não deve ser uma busca incessante por objetivos inalcançáveis, que muitas vezes nos faz duvidar da existência de Deus devido ao cansaço de correr contra a voz que nos diz que estamos sempre atrasados. 
Assim acredito firmemente que o propósito da vida reside em ter uma única relação e um único objetivo: conhecer a Deus. 
Crítico a tendência de buscar coisas que nos fazem perder tempo, que deveria ser investido em conhecer mais a Deus e em nos desapegarmos mais de nós mesmos. 
Temos mania de buscar por aquilo que não se interessa por nós e o fascínio por sermos reconhecidos por algo que não pode nos valorizar. 
A vida vai além de apenas se sentir bem e feliz; o propósito de cada sentimento, abraço e lugar é ter como centro a maravilha do coração de Jesus. O propósito da vida não é se casar, buscar satisfação máxima ou encontrar segurança no que podemos adquirir; talvez seja o oposto, perder tudo para encontrar verdadeira paz. A vida terrena não pode nos proporcionar o que nosso verdadeiro propósito pode, e a dedicação pela eternidade, em vez do passageiro para viver aquilo que Deus estabeleceu para nós.
.
.
.
.
.

Caption:
Our Edie had her big dance recital and her fan club all showed up to cheer her on.
She did amazing and shined on that stage. 
Our super-sized family almost took up an entire row. And you know the cheering, “EDIE!” was extra loud with this crew of ours (no filters)😜🫣🤣

I’m thankful for the love our family has for each other. It’s funny, you just never know how things are going to go with blended/extended families. 
And for a lot of years ours was a struggle. 
But as we asked JESUS to step into the center…miraculous changes began to happen. 
Hearts softened, forgiveness given/received, a loving/respectful bond formed. 
Truly something only JESUS could’ve brought about. 

Friends, I share all this because most of you only see the joyful happy moments I/people post online. Seeing everyone living their best lives can often fill people who are still in the thick of it with envy and sadness that their lives don’t look like that. 
I just wanted to remind you, cling to JESUS wherever you are in life, whatever struggle you’re facing, allow HIM into the center of your life and heart. HE truly brings beauty from ashes. He makes a way through impossible. 
HE makes all things new. 
✝️”Come to Me, all you who labor and are heavy laden, and I will give you rest. Take My yoke upon you and learn from Me, for I am gentle and lowly in heart, and you will find rest for your souls.”~Matthew 11:28-29
✝️”but you shall hold fast to the Lord your God, as you have done to this day.”~Joshua 23:8
✝️”Therefore, if anyone is in Christ, he is a new creation; old things have passed away; behold, all things have become new.”~2 Corinthians 5:17

Jump on the #ThankfulTrain what are you thankful for?

Caption:
A little reminder for those who feel like they’re constantly falling short:
You’re not a failure. You’re a learner.
Russell M. Nelson said, “Don’t demand of yourself things that are unreasonable, but demand of yourself improvement.
Perfection comes not in this life, but the next life. As you let the Lord help you through that, He will make the difference.”
You may be struggling right now...
Struggling with sin.
Struggling with addiction.
Struggling with weakness.
Struggling with negative habits.
Whatever it is you’re working through, don’t label yourself as a failure... you’re not. You’re learning. You’re trying. You’re figuring it out.
Just as a parent wouldn’t punish a child for falling down while learning to walk, our Father in Heaven sees us similarly.
Though He’s not pleased when we sin, He loves us infinitely and wants us to come home.
He wants us to focus on learning, growing, improving, and repenting/changing when we fall short.
As we bring our problems, sins, and troubles to Him, He will provide what we need to overcome and find strength. 🫶🏻 Credit @mrdrewyoung1  #hisgrace #comfort #peace #peaceinchrist #believeinchrist #christianart #believe #gospelthoughts #thechurchofjesuschristoflatterdaysaints #upliftingquotes #jesuschrist #savior #heavenlyfather #prayer #guidance #thoughtoftheday #christian #christianart #comefollowme #spiritual #strength #scriptures #bible #uplifting #thecomforter #jehovah

Caption:
17 years ago marks the Martyrdom of Fr. Ragheed Ganni and 3 Subdeacons.
‎قبل 17 سنة ذكرى استشهاد الأب رغيد گني و3 شمامسة
‎ܣܗܕܐ ܩܕܝܫܐ، ܡܨܠܐ ܒܕܠܢ 
Holy Martyrs, Pray for us
‎‏الشهداء المقدسين، صلوا لأجلنا

Ragheed Kani (January 20, 1972 - June 3, 2007) was an Iraqi priest, born in the city of Mosul, Iraq.
On June 3, 2007, Father Ragheed had finished celebrating the Eucharist Mass on Sunday evening, and because of the threats to his life, three deacons decided to accompany him. After the Mass, Father Ragheed walked away from the church, followed by Daoud, Esho, Bidaoud, and Esho’s wife in the car. They were intercepted by unknown gunmen. One of the gunmen shouted at Father Ragheed, saying that he had previously warned him to close the church and demanded to know why he did not do so. Father Ragheed replied, asking, “How can I close the house of God?” The gunmen ordered the woman to flee, then the gunmen shot the four men.
Father Ragheed was secretary to Bishop Boulos Faraj Rahho, Archbishop of Mosul for the Chaldean Church, the largest Christian denomination in Iraq. Raho was killed only nine months after the death of Father Ragheed, in the same city of Mosul.

رغيد كني (20 يناير 1972 - 3 يونيو 2007) كاهن عراقي ولد في مدينة الموصل، بالعراق.
‎في 3 يونيو 2007، كان الاب رغيد قد انتهى من الاحتفال بقداس القربانة المقدسة مساء الأحد،وبسبب التهديدات على حياته، قرر ثلاثة شمامسة مرافقته. بعد القداس، سار الاب رغيد بعيدًا عن الكنيسة ويتبعه (داود) و(إيشو) و(بيداود) وزوجة إيشو في السيارة؛ اعترضهم مسلحون مجهولون. صرخ أحد المسلحين في وجه الاب رغيد قائلاً إنه حذره سابقا بأن يغلق الكنيسة وطالبه بمعرفة سبب عدم قيامه بذلك. فأجاب الاب رغيد متسائلا “كيف يمكنني إغلاق بيت الله؟” أمر المسلحون المرأة بالفرار، ثم أطلق  المسلحون الرصاص على الرجال الاربعة.
‎كان الاب رغيد سكرتيرًا  للمطران لبولس فرج رحو، رئيس أساقفة الموصل للكنيسة الكلدانية، أكبر طائفة مسيحية في العراق. قُتل رحو بعد تسعة أشهر فقط من وفاة الاب رغيد ، في نفس مدينة الموصل.

Caption:
Reflecting this morning on the importance of Praise and Worship.

Psalm 100:2 says, “Worship the Lord with gladness; come before him with joyful songs.”

Praise and worship- especially musically - allows us to create an intimate space between US and the LORD. We often feel grounded and refreshed after spending time in deep worship with the Lord.

What are your favorite places to worship God to create this intimacy? OR… what is your favorite worship song?

For the Anchored Social team- we love worshiping in our cars, 🚗 and our current favorite song is “NOW” with Garrett Hornbuckle. (We know we’re biased, but the lyrics just HIT! 🔥) Share yours in the comments below!👇

Caption:
« A celui qui est ferme dans ses dispositions, tu assures une paix parfaite, parce qu’il se confie en toi » Esaïe‬ ‭26‬:‭3‬

La disposition c’est l’action de disposer, de mettre dans un certain ordre ; son résultat.

Nous voulons encourager une personne à tenir ferme dans ses dispositions. En prenant la table du Seigneur, Saint Cène, nous prenons de nouvelles décisions, de nouvelles dispositions pour cette semaine. 

Encourageons nous à tenir ferme, car le seigneur verra notre sincérité derrière notre disposition et il nous assurera une paix parfaite car c’est seulement en Dieu que nous la trouvons.

C’est en nous confiant en lui que nous serons dans la capacité de pouvoir tenir ferme. Voilà pourquoi nous souhaitons mettre tout notre cœur, toutes nos pensées, toutes nos décisions en Dieu et assurément que même dans nos prises de décision les plus difficiles. Le seigneur Jesus-christ sera capable de mettre cette paix en nous et avec cela nous marcherons en nouveauté de Vie 🙏🏿 

Amen bien ?

Caption:
Today after work was my first day back at the gym since my fall where I sprained my ankle back in January.

I walked a mile in 19:47 at a 3.0 speed which is 1 minute and 29 seconds slower and 0.3 slower than when I went to the gym 2 days before the sprain happened.

- Shoulder press is down to 25 lbs instead of 45. I did two sets of 10 reps.
- Pull down started at 100 lbs for a set and then I went down to 95 lbs for the second set. This actually has gotten better.

I’ll be honest: I am upset with the little set backs and I know they’re little. But, they’re still set backs and that’s what bugs me. I know I have to work myself back up to where I was at before and how much I was doing before. 

I’m also trying to give myself grace because my body was a bit tired since shuttle came at work which involves unloading inventory from it and loading things to be sent out on it. So, I had already done some working out.

Comment "Amen" if you believe that.

Caption:
- Méditation spéciale cette semaine sur le thème « Instruire l’enfant selon la voie qu’il doit suivre. »

Sujet : Isaac, un enfant obéissant.

Verset : Genèse 22:9 – Lorsqu’ils furent arrivés au lieu que Dieu lui avait dit, Abraham y éleva un autel, et rangea le bois. Il lia son fils Isaac, et le mit sur l’autel, par-dessus le bois.

Leçon : Le chapitre 22 du livre de Genèse nous présente une histoire très instructive tant qu’aux adultes qu’aux adolescents. Il nous raconte l’histoire d’Abraham qui a été mis à l’épreuve par Dieu qui lui a ordonné d’offrir en holocauste son fils Isaac. Nous n’allons pas nous attarder sur Abraham car celui qui nous intéresse particulièrement, c’est Isaac.

Pendant qu’ils étaient en route pour le sacrifice, Isaac qui connaissait déjà les composantes et comment offrir un holocauste à Dieu, demanda à son père: où est l’holocauste ? Puisque qu’il n’avait pas vu d’animal, il avait dejà une idée de ce qui va se passer. Arrivé au lieu où Dieu avait indiqué à Abraham, ce dernier y éleva un autel, lia son fils et le mit là-dessus pour l’offrir en sacrifice. Isaac, voyant tout ce qui se passe, n’a même pas essayé de se rebeller ou de désobéir à son père. Il a accepté de se soumettre à tout ce que son père allait lui faire.

Obéir à Dieu c’est être d’accord d’aller jusqu’au bout avec Lui, certes Isaac était un enfant mais il croyait et obéissait à Dieu. Cependant, pour honorer son père et sa mère, l’enfant doit connaître la Parole de Dieu qui le lui recommande, et être capable de le faire dans l’esprit. Honorer son père et sa mère, ça veut dire lui obéir selon le Seigneur. De ce fait, un enfant obéissant est une vraie offrande à Dieu, car il fait d’abord preuve d’une dépendance et soumission totale envers celui en qui Il croit.

À retenir : La connaissance et la soumission de l’enfant à la parole de Dieu, est une garantie à l’obéissance tant recherchée dans la vie de chaque enfant. L’enfant qui obéit aux ordonnances divines obéira plus facilement à ses parents, car il reconnaîtra leur autorité.

Caption:
He is found in the waiting.⁠
⁠
I used to think that I was all alone in times of waiting for God to fulfill a promise or for a prophetic word to come to pass. I felt like the “delay” was coupled with God pulling away part of himself. Like he was still there, but it felt like he was only half there since he wasn’t doing what he said he would do. At least not in the timing I wanted.⁠
⁠
I have learned, though, that as I fully trust in his timing and his ways he is closer than ever. I was so focused on what is to come that I was missing what he was doing in the here and now. ⁠
⁠
If you are waiting on God to fulfill a word or promise in your life, I know it can get hard in the waiting, but I want to encourage you today to notice what he is doing in the here and now. Don’t miss out on the beauty of his Spirit breathing on you in the daily moments. Slow down and allow him to show you himself in the small things. I promise it will take your breath away!⁠
⁠
#Jesus #faith #hope #waiting #waitontheLord #promisesofGod #itsthesmallthings #christian #lifewithJesus

Caption:
"Is any sick among you? Let him call for the priests of the church; and let them pray over him, anointing him with oil in the name of the Lord"

This morning I received the Sacrament of the Anointing of the Sick in preparation for some intensive medical testing later this week. I'm worried. Yes. I know I don't need to be, and God is in control, but human anxiety gets in the way of trust. 

This Sacrament was such a comfort to me. Hearing the beautiful words...

"Through this holy anointing, may the Lord in his love and mercy help you with the grace of the Holy Spirit." 

And,

"May the Lord who frees you from sin save you and raise you up. Amen" 

...is such a comfort. I'm not alone. Christ is with me. He's my healer, my lover, my God. And nothing that happens to me is without His knowledge and guidance. 

If you are someone who lives in pain, or is ill, in mind, body, or soil, please, please ask for the Sacrament of the Sick. It's not only for those who are dying, but to raise the parts of us who are living to fullness of life. God works miracles, friends. He wants to heal us 🤍

So this week, please pray for me, and for my little sister, as we undergo this testing and hopefully get some more answers. 

Trust in God. Trust that healing and wholeness are  His desires for you. 

"Whatever God wants. " - Saint Gianna Molla

Caption:
FAITH RXD | June 2024 | Discipline and Discipleship 

Join us this Saturday to take part in a free workout at ION Strength and Conditioning facility in Cardiff and learn these principles you can apply to your life right away.
 
We start at 1100 and will run for about 60 mins.
 
Where is it?
ION Strength and Conditioning, Cheviot Close, Llanishen, Cardiff, CF14 5JA (opposite the Royal Mail depot).
 
When is it?
This Saturday (8 June 2024) 1100. Come in a little earlier for a coffee at @ioncardiff @yellowchaircoffee
 
What do I need to bring?
Wear some gym gear if you’ve got it, a small towel, and a bottle of water with you.
 
How much does it cost?
The session is completely FREE.
 
Do I have to be fit or a member of a gym to take part?
No, we welcome people of all ages, abilities, and experience levels.
 
What if I’m not religious?
Don’t worry about it, as we’re all at different stages in our lives. Come along with an open mind to receive the encouragement of the day.
 
Please get in touch if you’ve got any other questions you’d like to ask us.

Caption:
Polish soccer fans protested the decision by the far-left mayor of Warsaw to remove crucifixes from Warsaw’s city hall in the historically Catholic country.

In a match between Legia Warsaw and Zaglebie Lubin last Saturday, Legia Warsaw fans showed a banner that read “Trzaskowski, hands off the cross.” The sign was a protest against Warsaw Mayor Rafal Trzaskowski’s decision to ban religious symbols in the city hall under the pretense of “equal treatment.”

A spokesperson for the mayor stated that Warsaw would be the first city to adopt the ban on religious symbols, i.e., crosses and crucifixes, in a public building. In the same document, the mayor also urged employees to use transgender “pronouns” and treat homosexual “couples” as if they were “married,” even though homosexual unions are not legally recognized in Poland.

Conservative politicians also expressed their criticism, and some took legal action against the ban. According to Euractiv, MP Malgorzata Gosiewska from the Law and Justice Party (PiS), the former governing party of Poland, submitted a request to the local administration to declare the mayor of Warsaw’s decree illegal.

PiS leader Jarosław Kaczyński accused Trzaskowski’s party and its European group, the nominally “Christian democratic” European People’s Party (EPP), of trying to erase religion from people’s lives, as they seek “to destroy religion, destroy what people believe, that they are more than just homo sapiens, that they are human beings who have a soul, that they are human beings made in the image and likeness of God.”
